<p>I'm using Padrino, and I want to take parameters out of URL and use them in an <code>.erb</code> template.</p>  <p>In my app setup I have:</p>  <pre><code>get '/testpage/:id' do   userID = params[:id]   render 'test/index' end </code></pre>  <p>In my <code>test/</code> folder I have <code>index.html.erb</code> which is successfully rendered, for a url like <code>http://localhost:9000/testpage/hello123</code>.</p>  <p>However, I've tried printing the <code>userID</code> param on the page with:</p>  <pre><code> &lt;%= @userID %&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The rest of the page renders fine but <code>hello123</code> isn't anywhere to be found. When I try <code>&lt;%= userID %&gt;</code> I get <code>undefined local variable or method</code>userID' for #`</p>  <p>What am I missing here?</p>